title: Traffic disruption expected due to slow moving load | Border
text:
Credit: Press Association Police are warning motorists to expect traffic disruption in north Cumbria tomorrow.
An abnormal load is being escorted from Carlisle to Blenkinsopp in Northumberland via the A689 into Crosby Village and onto the A69.
The load will start to be moved at around 9am and police say drivers should expect delays until 1pm.
Last updated Wed 23 Sep 2015 Travel Cumbria Traffic Roads
